  "text": "The 5′flanking region of the candidate gene was amplified using genomic DNA extracted from roots of E. grandis using a CTAB method [CITATION_1] ) and the Universal GenomeWalker Kit (Clontech) following the manufacturer's instructions. For this, two gene-specific primers (HAK-GSP1-5′CTT CAT GTT TAG CTT GGT CTT CTC C3′ and HAK-GSP2 -5′GTG ATC TCT GAC TCT TCT TCT TCC TC3′) were designed based on the nucleotide sequence of the starting EST clone. The longest amplification product (~ 1.3 kb) obtained was gel-purified, cloned into pGEMTeasy (Promega) and sequenced using the BigDye Terminator v3.1 Sequencing Standard Kit (Applied Biosystems) and an automated ABI Prism 377 sequencer (Applied Biosystems).",
